{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the interaction process involves two stages:• Initial stage: At the begining, agent should first interpret the data and propose tasks that make the goal executable by mapping it to the data.",
    "The principle is to identify data variables and task type.",
    "For instance, for a goal of \"find high-risk events in a city\", useful data variables could include time, space, text, and sentiment.",
    "The agent also needs to distinguish the purpose of the analysis, e.g., \"finding outliers\".",
    "Thus, different combinations of data variables and task types can form different tasks under a goal."
  ]
}